# Type Definition Patterns

All feature types live in `src/shared/types/{feature}.types.ts`.

## Required Types for Each Feature

```typescript
import { EnumType } from '@prisma/client';

// 1. Database Model Type
export type Feature = {
  id: string;
  field1: string;
  field2: EnumType;
  dateField: Date;
  optionalField: string | null;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
};

// 2. Create Request (input for POST)
export interface CreateFeatureRequest {
  field1: string;
  field2: EnumType;
  dateField: Date | string;  // Accept both
  optionalField?: string | null;
}

// 3. Update Request (input for PUT - all optional)
export interface UpdateFeatureRequest {
  field1?: string;
  field2?: EnumType;
  dateField?: Date | string;
  optionalField?: string | null;
}

// 4. Response Type (API output - dates as strings)
export interface FeatureResponse {
  id: string;
  field1: string;
  field2: EnumType;
  dateField: string;  // ISO string
  optionalField: string | null;
  createdAt: string;  // ISO string
  updatedAt: string;  // ISO string
}

// Re-export Prisma enums
export { EnumType };
```

## Date Handling

```typescript
// ✅ Database model: Date objects
type Model = {
  birthDate: Date;
  deathDate: Date | null;
};

// ✅ Request: Accept both Date and string
interface CreateRequest {
  birthDate: Date | string;
  deathDate?: Date | string | null;
}

// ✅ Response: ISO strings
interface Response {
  birthDate: string;
  deathDate: string | null;
}
```

## Naming Conventions

- `{Feature}` - Database model
- `Create{Feature}Request` - Creation input
- `Update{Feature}Request` - Update input  
- `{Feature}Response` - API response
- `{Feature}ErrorResponse` - Error format (if custom)

## Import Prisma Types

```typescript
// ✅ Import enums and types from Prisma
import { Gender, RelationshipType } from '@prisma/client';

// Re-export for convenience
export { Gender, RelationshipType };
```
